    <ul id="roadmap" class="columned">
      <li>
        <p>We're working towards building the perfect IDE to make building HTML5 applications as enjoyable for you as possible.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <h4><i class="icon-th-large"></i> Code Editing</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Multi pane code editing</li>
                  <li>Instant preview window</li>
                  <li>Rich Find, Search &amp; Replace etc. including regex support</li>
                  <li>Code completion linked to function help</li>
                  <li>Hyperlink to function defined at cursor location</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h4><i class="icon-th-large"></i> HTML, CSS, JS Preprocessor support</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>HAML, Markdown</li>
                  <li>LESS, SCSS</li>
                  <li>Coffeescript</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h4><i class="icon-th-large"></i> Codio Collaboration</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Tight integration with Git and Mercurial</li>
                  <li>Chat windows with recording for real-time code editing</li>
                  <li>Voice chat for real-time editing</li>
                  <li>Star, watch, rate and explore</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h4><i class="icon-th-large"></i> Deployment &amp; Building</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Define multiple deployment points within the Codio platform (staging, production etc.)</li>
                  <li>Deploy to FTP, SFTP</li>
                  <li>Deploy to Heroku</li>
                  <li>Options to minify (etc) upon deployment</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
              <li>
                <h4><i class="icon-th-large"></i> Widgets &amp; UI Builder</h4>
                <ul>
                  <li>Open Widget framework allowing HTML widgets to be mapped to Property &amp; Event toolbars</li>
                  <li>Widget definition to be done as a standard Codio project, making them shareable</li>
                  <li>Automatic tie-in between selected HTML and Property &amp; Event toolbars</li>
                  <li>Drag and Drop UI Builder</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>

        </ul>
      </li>
